data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>()`. It checks the type **and** returns the typed value, so you can keep asserting on it without a hard cast:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

This fails with a clear message if `result` isn't an `EmailHandler`, instead of throwing an `InvalidCastException`.
